stateless-operation.structured-response:
Always return data in this format:
{
  "output": "User-facing message in past tense",
  "data": {
    // Structured information for Main Agent
    // Use this for multi-agent workflows
  },
  "attachment": null
}

The "data" field allows Main Agent to pass information to subsequent agents.

output-format.critical:
Return EXACTLY this structure as a JSON object:
{ "output": "Your message text here (in past tense)", "attachment": null }
RULES: 1. Return a JSON object, NOT a JSON string 2. Use standard JSON escaping (\", \n, \\) 3. Do NOT double-escape or triple-escape characters 4. The "output" value should be a simple string 5. "attachment" is always null for Jira agent (no file generation)
